      • onSearchParts

        public void onSearchParts​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        RUNTIME ERROR: When creating the onSearchParts method there were issues with having the partial matches with searches. After meeting with the professor and rewatching the webinar on how to create searches I discovered that my search was looking for exact matches using partList.getSelectionModel().select(p). After discussions with the professor I refactored my code to a "(String.valueOf(part.getId()).contains(searchString) || part.getName().contains(searchString))" which allowed for partial matches. This method searches the Parts inventory. If a partial match is found for either the part name or the partID then it will populate the list. If no match is found an error message will appear. If you hit enter on an empty search then the entire list of parts will repopulate.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - user clicks the search textfield in the parts section.

      • onSearchProducts

        public void onSearchProducts​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        This method searches the Products inventory. If a partial match is found for either the product name or the productId then it will populate the list. If no match is found an error message will appear. If you hit enter on an empty search then the entire list of Products will repopulate.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - user clicks the Search Text field in the products section.
